				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hat{Y}$$\end{document}) and 95% CIs are reported.

Pooled IMC estimates from the EMG signals for each group are represented graphically, along with the percentage of trials with significant coherence at each identified frequency. The pooled coherence score for an individual frequency is considered significant when the estimate is greater than the 95% confidence limit (CL). The CLs were calculated from the number of segments (L) included in each coherence estimate, using the method from Halliday et al. (1995):3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
